OL,3,CCouncil threatens #100 fines for
OL,4,Cswearing in public after beach fights
OL,6,FBut the authority is being accused of
OL,7,Fexceeding its powers with the
OL,8,Fthreatened fines for bad language, and
OL,9,Fcritics include Kent's Police and
OL,10,FCrime Commissioner.
OL,12,FHowever, the leader of the council has
OL,13,Fcalled recent reporting on the order
OL,14,F"a mountain of nonsense" as they
OL,15,Fbacked new plans to protect public
OL,16,Fspaces.
OL,18,FAt a cabinet meeting in Margate on
OL,19,FThursday evening, councillors
OL,20,Fcomplained of "misleading" reporting
OL,21,Fabout the new order.
